text:
H.S. Football: Morris Catholic Crusaders crushed October 21, 2015 Last updated: Wednesday, October 21, 2015, 12:31 AM Neighbor News (Denville Edition) Print 
On Oct. 10, Butlerâ€™s Bulldogs took a 14-7 win over the Morris Catholic Crusaders in overtime. Here, Morris Catholic Peter Palumbo (24) pushes for extra yardage after being taken down by Butler players. Morris Catholics next home game will be on Saturday, Nov. 7, at 2:45 p.m. against Wallkill Valley.During half time, Morris Catholic Seniors Sean Mollahan and Julia Rossetto were named the Homecoming King and Queen.
